# Content Production Batch Standards

## Weekly Content Volume (Non-Negotiable)

Every week in a production batch must contain exactly 12 pieces:

| Channel | Pieces per Week | Format |
|---------|----------------|--------|
| Anchor blog post | 1 | Long-form article, signs off "Capably Yours, Jared" |
| Podcast script | 1 | Solo episode (max 25 min), also distributed as YouTube video |
| LinkedIn posts | 5 | Professional insight posts, no sign-off |
| Facebook posts | 5 | Warmer/personal tone, no sign-off |

## File Naming Convention

```
week-N-blog-slug.md
week-N-podcast-slug.md
week-N-linkedin-1.md through week-N-linkedin-5.md
week-N-facebook-1.md through week-N-facebook-5.md
```

## File Template (All Content Types)

1. **Title** (H1)
2. **Post Metadata** -- Type, Week, Theme, Quarterly plan reference, Strategic context
3. **Visual Assets** -- Image type, Rationale, AI image prompt (9-point standard, Capable Wealth palette only), Text overlay, Platform/dimensions
4. **Full content draft** -- Jared's voice per voice-profile.md and content-recipe.md
5. **Quality Checklist** -- Voice Alignment, Audience Specificity, Relevance Validation, Pull Signal Design, Visual Assets

## Podcast Script Structure

Podcast scripts replace the old YouTube script format. Structure:

- **COLD OPEN** (30-60s) -- Hook that pulls the listener in immediately
- **INTRO AND CONTEXT** (1-2 min) -- Set the stakes, why this matters now
- **MAIN SEGMENTS** (3-5 segments, each 3-5 min) -- Core teaching, math examples, frameworks
- **LISTENER TAKEAWAY** (1-2 min) -- Actionable summary, one thing to do this week
- **PHILOSOPHICAL CLOSE** (1-2 min) -- Connect to bigger life principles

Tone: Conversational, exploratory, Jared thinking out loud with the listener. More depth and nuance than blog. Audio must stand alone; video version is a different consumption angle.

Visual asset: Podcast cover art card (1400x1400 for podcast feeds, 1280x720 variant for YouTube thumbnail).

## Social Post Expansion

When the quarterly plan briefs fewer than 5 posts for a channel, create additional posts by:
- Isolating individual talking points from the anchor/podcast as standalone insights
- Creating story-driven variations (especially for Facebook)
- Adding action prompts ("one question to ask", "calculate this number")
- Building week-to-week narrative continuity

